    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="9">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302540">Figure 40</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302540" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302540" filename="../figg13/g1302540.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 40. Shifter Housing Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut lockwire and remove machined bolt from the 1st and reverse shift block (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302541">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302541" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302541" filename="../figg13/g1302541.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 41. Remove Machined Bolt From 1st and Reverse Shift Block</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount housing in a vise as indicated using caution to avoid marring machined surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302542">Figure 42</hotlnk>). Cut lockwire, remove lockscrews and remove direct yoke
                bar and block from housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302542" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302542" filename="../figg13/g1302542.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 42. Remove Direct Yoke Bar</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>When removing bars, remaining bars must be kept in neutral position or interlock parts will
                    prevent removal.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut lockwire, and remove the lockscrew and the 4th-5th speed yoke, bar and spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302543">Figure 43</hotlnk>). As the bar is pulled out of the housing, remove the
                interlock pin from the bar (inset).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302543" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302543" filename="../figg13/g1302543.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 43. Remove 4th-5th Speed Yoke, Bar and Spacer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut lockwires, remove lockscrews, and remove 2nd &#38; 3rd speed yoke and block (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302544">Figure 44</hotlnk>). Remove the interlock pin from the bar as it clears the
                housing boss (inset).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302544" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302544" filename="../figg13/g1302544.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 44. Remove 2nd and 3rd Speed Yoke and Block</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut lockwires, remove lockscrews, and remove the 1st-reverse finger, bar and block from the
                housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302545">Figure 45</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302545" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302545" filename="../figg13/g1302545.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 45. Remove 1st-Reverse Finger, Bar and Block</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove three interlock balls from the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302546">Figure 46</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302546" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302546" filename="../figg13/g1302546.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 46. Remove Interlock Balls From Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the snap ring, retainer, spring and plunger from 1st and reverse block
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302547">inset, Figure 47</hotlnk>). Use caution as the plug is spring loaded.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302547" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302547" filename="../figg13/g1302547.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 47. Remove Snap Ring, Retainer, Spring and Plunger</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, remove the plug from 6th &#38; 7th block (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302548">inset, Figure 48</hotlnk>). Remove spring and plunger.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302548" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302548" filename="../figg13/g1302548.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 48. Remove Plug From 6th-7th Block</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
